# Figma -> Flutter Rules (Hexa-cam)

- Implement UI in Flutter widgets, not web stacks (no React/Tailwind/CSS output).
- Preserve `GetX` patterns: route via `GetMaterialApp` and state via existing controllers/providers.
- Reuse theme tokens from `lib/config/theme.dart` (`AppTheme.*`) before adding new colors/styles.
- Prefer shared UI in `lib/ui/common/` and keep feature screens in existing feature folders.
- Keep dark theme consistency (`AppTheme.darkTheme`) unless a task explicitly adds another theme.
- Use Material icons first; use `flutter_svg` only when a real SVG asset is required.
- Keep responsive behavior consistent with current mobile-first layouts and existing tablet/desktop checks.
- Do not hardcode duplicated design tokens in page widgets when an `AppTheme` token exists.
- Keep animation timings aligned with theme durations (`transitionFast`, `transitionBase`, `transitionSlow`).
- For forms/buttons/dialogs, match existing decoration helpers (`panelDecoration`, `softCardDecoration`).

## Project anchors

- App shell: `lib/app.dart`
- DI/service registry: `lib/state/app_registry.dart`
- Theme/tokens: `lib/config/theme.dart`
- Primary feature areas: `lib/features/`, `lib/ui/`, `lib/controllers/`, `lib/data/`

## Done criteria for Figma-driven changes

- New UI compiles in Flutter without introducing alternate UI frameworks.
- Colors/spacing/typography map to `AppTheme` constants where possible.
- Shared widgets extracted when the same pattern appears in multiple screens.
- Existing flows (camera, viewer, report, auth) keep behavior parity unless task says otherwise.
